WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.100
♪ WHEN THIS BOY
MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.100 --> 00:06.000
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:10.767
♪ WANDERING DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.767 --> 00:12.667
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.667 --> 00:14.567
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.567 --> 00:18.800
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS
STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.800 --> 00:21.367
♪ WHEN THIS BOY
MEETS WORLD ♪

00:24.867 --> 00:26.834
CORY, MR. RUTHERFORD CALLED
FROM THE BANQUET HALL.

00:26.834 --> 00:28.600
SOMEBODY CANCELED, AND NOW
THERE'S AN OPEN DATE.

00:28.600 --> 00:31.200
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO GET MARRIED
ON JULY 4th,

00:31.200 --> 00:32.834
INDEPENDENCE DAY?

00:32.834 --> 00:35.767
MARRIED ON INDEPENDENCE DAY?
HOW IRONIC.

00:35.767 --> 00:38.567
YOU'RE NOT GETTING
COLD FEET ABOUT THIS,
ARE YOU?

00:38.567 --> 00:41.100
TOPANGA, YOU KNOW
THOSE TERRIBLE DREAMS
I'VE BEEN HAVING?

00:41.100 --> 00:42.400
YEAH.
WELL, THEY'RE--

00:42.400 --> 00:44.100
DON'T GET MAD--
ABOUT MARRIAGE.

00:44.100 --> 00:46.400
THEY'RE--DON'T GET MAD--
ANTI-MARRIAGE DREAMS.

00:46.400 --> 00:49.233
YOU--DON'T GET MAD--
YOU DON'T COME OUT SO WELL.

00:49.233 --> 00:50.900
WHY NOT?

00:50.900 --> 00:52.400
WELL, LAST NIGHT,
FOR EXAMPLE,
I HAD THIS DREAM

00:52.400 --> 00:54.300
THAT YOU AND I,
WE GOT MARRIED,

00:54.300 --> 00:56.500
AND WE WOUND UP
IN THE POOR HOUSE.

00:56.500 --> 00:58.133
YOU KNOW HOW I KNOW?

00:58.133 --> 00:59.867
BIG, BIG SIGN
ON THE FRONT--

00:59.867 --> 01:01.667
"THE POOR HOUSE."

01:01.667 --> 01:03.934
AND INSIDE,
IT SOUNDED LIKE

01:03.934 --> 01:05.567
PEOPLE WERE--WERE
BEING BEATEN,

01:05.567 --> 01:07.900
AND THERE WAS
THIS EXECUTION ROOM

01:07.900 --> 01:09.367
CALLED THE TOPANGA ROOM,

01:09.367 --> 01:11.834
AND THE EXECUTIONER
WAS YOU,

01:11.834 --> 01:13.400
AND ALL
THE CHOPPED-OFF HEADS

01:13.400 --> 01:15.734
IN THE HEAD BASKET
WERE ME!

01:15.734 --> 01:17.367
ARE WE GETTING
MARRIED OR NOT?

01:17.367 --> 01:18.967
YEAH, I'M JUST TALKING.

01:18.967 --> 01:21.133
BUT HOW ARE YOU
SO SURE ABOUT THIS?

01:21.133 --> 01:22.967
BECAUSE I LOOK
AT OUR PARENTS, CORY.

01:22.967 --> 01:24.700
I MEAN, THEY GOT MARRIED
WHEN THEY WERE YOUNG,

01:24.700 --> 01:27.667
AND THEY LOVE
EACH OTHER MORE NOW
THAN THEY EVER DID.

01:27.667 --> 01:28.900
YEAH, I GUESS
YOU'RE RIGHT.

01:28.900 --> 01:31.500
I MEAN, MY PARENTS
ARE STILL HAVING
BABIES.

01:31.500 --> 01:33.500
OH, BY THE WAY,
MY PARENTS ARE
COMING INTO TOWN

01:33.500 --> 01:34.867
TO DISCUSS THE WEDDING.

01:34.867 --> 01:38.500
"OH, BY THE WAY,
MY PARENTS ARE
COMING INTO TOWN"?

01:38.500 --> 01:40.667
OH, BY THE WAY,
CAPTAIN TITANIC,

01:40.667 --> 01:42.467
THIS SHIP'S
IN 2 PIECES!

01:42.467 --> 01:44.600
I WANNA BE ABLE
TO TELL THEM
WE'VE SET THE DATE.

01:44.600 --> 01:45.867
WE HAVE?

01:45.867 --> 01:47.800
CORY, IT'S OK
TO BE NERVOUS ABOUT THIS.

01:47.800 --> 01:48.800
IT'S NATURAL.

01:48.800 --> 01:51.000
HEY. YOU WANNA
HEAR SOMETHING?

01:51.000 --> 01:54.400
FEENY AND I ARE
GETTING MARRIED
SUNDAY.

01:57.667 --> 01:58.667
ARE YOU
NERVOUS?

02:00.967 --> 02:02.300
[WHISPERING]
Yes.

02:06.200 --> 02:07.667
WE'RE JUST PLANNING
A SIMPLE CEREMONY

02:07.667 --> 02:09.767
AT THE JUSTICE
OF THE PEACE
ON SUNDAY.

02:09.767 --> 02:11.734
OH, ALAN, WE SHOULD
HAVE THE WEDDING HERE.

02:11.734 --> 02:14.000
OH, NO, NO.
THAT'S NOT NECESSARY.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.934
COME ON, GEORGE.
EVERYONE WILL WANT TO BE THERE.

02:15.934 --> 02:17.867
YOU CAN'T ROB THEM
OF THAT.

02:17.867 --> 02:20.500
I CAN'T IMAGINE
ANYBODY BEING
INTERESTED IN US.

02:20.500 --> 02:23.667
I'M SURPRISED <i>SHE'S  </i>
INTERESTED IN US.

02:23.667 --> 02:25.300
OH, GEORGE.

02:25.300 --> 02:26.400
OH, LILA.

02:26.400 --> 02:27.400
OH, MY.

02:27.400 --> 02:29.400
OH, BOY!

02:29.400 --> 02:31.500
BIG TROUBLE!

02:31.500 --> 02:33.567
CORY, MR. FEENY AND LILA
ARE GETTING MARRIED

02:33.567 --> 02:34.667
IN OUR LIVING ROOM.

02:34.667 --> 02:36.567
I'M THRILLED
FOR YOU, FEENY.

02:36.567 --> 02:37.700
NOW GET OUT

02:37.700 --> 02:38.900
AND TAKE
YOUR CHICK WITH YOU.

02:38.900 --> 02:41.133
CORY, HAVE YOU
LOST YOUR MIND?

02:41.133 --> 02:43.900
THE IN-LAWS ARE COMING.

02:43.900 --> 02:45.033
WE'RE OUTTA HERE.

02:45.033 --> 02:46.300
LOOKING FORWARD
TO SUNDAY.

02:46.300 --> 02:47.600
YES, YES,
WE ALL ARE.

02:47.600 --> 02:49.000
NOW, LET'S GO.

02:49.000 --> 02:50.500
YOU'RE
A GOOD BOY.

02:52.000 --> 02:53.500
BIG TROUBLE!

02:53.500 --> 02:54.500
OH, CORY,

02:54.500 --> 02:56.300
IT'S JUST
TOPANGA'S PARENTS.

02:56.300 --> 02:59.300
WELL, I'M GOING
IN THE LIVING ROOM.

03:03.500 --> 03:05.767
THEY USED TO BE
TOPANGA'S PARENTS.

03:05.767 --> 03:07.567
NOW THEY'RE THE IN-LAWS.

03:07.567 --> 03:09.500
NOW THEY HATE ME.
WHY?

03:09.500 --> 03:12.100
THE SAME REASON
GRANDMA HATES YOU.

03:12.100 --> 03:13.400
OH, GOT IT.

03:13.400 --> 03:14.800
AND OTHER REASONS.

03:14.800 --> 03:16.100
WHAT OTHER REASONS?

03:16.100 --> 03:17.133
YALE.

03:17.133 --> 03:18.200
I'M THE REASON
THAT THEIR DAUGHTER

03:18.200 --> 03:19.233
IS NOT GOING
TO YALE THIS YEAR.

03:19.233 --> 03:21.033
I'M ALSO THE REASON
THAT THEIR DAUGHTER

03:21.033 --> 03:22.700
IS NOT LIVING WITH THEM
IN PITTSBURGH.

03:22.700 --> 03:25.133
THAT IS WHY
I MADE THESE.

03:27.133 --> 03:29.300
DOS AND DON'TS
FOR BEHAVIOR
AROUND THE IN-LAWS?

03:29.300 --> 03:31.300
WHAT, YOU DIDN'T THINK
I WAS ACTUALLY GONNA LET YOU

03:31.300 --> 03:33.233
BE YOURSELVES FOR THIS,
DID YA?

03:33.233 --> 03:34.967
"NO IMPRESSIONS,
NONE."

03:34.967 --> 03:38.000
WHAT?
PEOPLE LOVE
MY IMPRESSIONS.

03:38.000 --> 03:42.000
OH, PLEASE. NO ONE
EVEN KNOWS WHEN
YOU'RE DOING ONE.

03:42.000 --> 03:43.100
FINE.

03:43.100 --> 03:45.133
[BABY CRIES]

03:47.600 --> 03:51.367
♪ HUSH, LITTLE BABY,
DON'T SAY A WORD ♪

03:51.367 --> 03:54.867
♪ MAMA'S GONNA BUY YOU
A MOCKINGBIRD ♪

03:54.867 --> 03:57.300
UH, NO SHE AIN'T, MA.
NOT TONIGHT.

03:57.300 --> 03:59.133
HA.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, HA?

03:59.133 --> 04:00.734
I MEAN, HA,
YOU CAN'T SING.

04:00.734 --> 04:03.400
I MEAN, NO,
YOU SING VERY WELL.
BUT NOT TONIGHT,

04:03.400 --> 04:05.600
'CAUSE IT'S
ON THE "DON'T" LIST
LIKE MY IMPRESSIONS.

04:07.367 --> 04:09.934
[DOORBELL RINGS]
AAH! THEY'RE HERE!

04:09.934 --> 04:13.367
OH, CORY, THERE'S
NOTHING TO BE
NERVOUS ABOUT.

04:13.367 --> 04:15.700
THEIR DAUGHTER LOVES YOU.
THAT'S WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

04:15.700 --> 04:18.033
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THAT'S WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

04:18.033 --> 04:19.700
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
IS IMPORTANT?

04:19.700 --> 04:21.967
THAT YOU TWO STICK TO
THE CONVERSATIONAL TOPICS

04:21.967 --> 04:23.734
THAT I'VE CLEARLY
WRITTEN OUT FOR YOU.

04:23.734 --> 04:26.567
"BRIDGES
AND PATIO FURNITURE"?

04:26.567 --> 04:27.900
"PEACHES AND SLIPCOVERS."

04:27.900 --> 04:29.600
THAT'S IT! NOTHING ELSE!

04:29.600 --> 04:33.400
NOBODY SAYS
ANYTHING STUPID, OK?

04:33.400 --> 04:35.100
Nothing stupid.

04:37.100 --> 04:39.567
[ALL]
HI.

04:39.567 --> 04:43.000
I'M SORRY YOUR DAUGHTER
GAVE UP YALE FOR ME.

04:43.000 --> 04:44.700
CORY, YOU REMEMBER
MY PARENTS,

04:44.700 --> 04:46.000
JEDEDIAH
AND RHIANNON.

04:46.000 --> 04:47.900
IT'S OK, CORY.
SHE'S HAPPY WHERE SHE IS.

04:47.900 --> 04:49.300
SURE, WHAT THE HELL.

04:49.300 --> 04:52.000
4 GENERATIONS OF LAWRENCES
AT YALE ARE PLENTY. HA HA.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.600
[NERVOUS LAUGHTER]

04:54.600 --> 04:55.967
WOULD YOU LIKE TO COME IN?

04:55.967 --> 04:57.300
YEAH.
I GUESS.

04:58.600 --> 04:59.934
HI.
HELLO, CORY.

05:01.400 --> 05:04.600
WHITE BALL
IN THE HOLE
RIGHT OVER THERE.

05:04.600 --> 05:06.000
WHEE.

05:06.000 --> 05:08.133
ERIC, YOU JUST
SCRATCHED ON PURPOSE.

05:08.133 --> 05:11.700
YEAH, WELL, I'M
A LOSER ANYWAY.

05:17.033 --> 05:18.867
HEY, DO YOU WANNA TALK?

05:20.233 --> 05:21.934
WHAT, YOU AND ME?

05:21.934 --> 05:25.600
YEAH. CAN WE DO THAT?

05:25.600 --> 05:27.467
WHY, I MEAN,
I DON'T KNOW.

05:27.467 --> 05:29.467
WE NEVER HAVE BEFORE.

05:29.467 --> 05:31.667
NO, NOT IN
THE LAST 6 YEARS.

05:31.667 --> 05:33.100
NOT EVEN THAT YEAR
WE LIVED TOGETHER.

05:33.100 --> 05:35.133
I KNOW.
I COMPLETELY FORGOT
ABOUT THAT YEAR.

05:35.133 --> 05:37.767
WHEN WAS THAT?
THAT WAS...LAST YEAR.

05:39.600 --> 05:41.600
OH!
OH!

05:41.600 --> 05:44.233
SO, YOU WANT TO TRY TALKING
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS?

05:44.233 --> 05:47.867
WHAT COULD YOU AND I
POSSIBLY HAVE
TO TALK ABOUT?

05:49.233 --> 05:51.100
OK.

05:51.100 --> 05:53.200
MY LIFE SUCKS, SHAWNIE.

05:53.200 --> 05:56.400
I LOST MY APARTMENT--
MY APARTMENT!

05:56.400 --> 05:58.500
I LOST RACHEL--RACHEL!

05:58.500 --> 06:00.233
I LOST
MY BEST FRIEND JACK.

06:00.233 --> 06:01.834
RACHEL!

06:01.834 --> 06:05.200
AND NOW I'M ABOUT
TO LOSE FEENY TO
THAT MEAN OLD LADY.

06:05.200 --> 06:06.600
JACK!

06:09.500 --> 06:13.400
WELL, ERIC, I LOST
SOMETHING THAT MEANS MORE
TO ME THAN ANY OF THAT,

06:13.400 --> 06:15.200
AND I MANAGED
TO SURVIVE.

06:15.200 --> 06:17.500
YOU MEAN
YOUR DEAD DAD, SHAWN?

06:17.500 --> 06:19.934
YOU'RE A SENSITIVE GUY.

06:19.934 --> 06:21.767
HEY, THANKS, MAN.

06:21.767 --> 06:25.033
OH, I JUST WISH THAT
RACHEL COULD SEE THAT.

06:25.033 --> 06:26.667
I MEAN, I LOVE HER.

06:26.667 --> 06:28.200
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

06:28.200 --> 06:31.300
DO YOU THINK THE TWO OF YOU
WOULD ACTUALLY MAKE
A GOOD COUPLE?

06:31.300 --> 06:33.500
SHE'S SO PRETTY.

06:33.500 --> 06:36.800
RIGHT. BUT WHAT ABOUT HER
ATTRACTS YOU SPIRITUALLY?

06:36.800 --> 06:40.200
OH, SPIRITUALLY.
SHE'S SO PRETTY.

06:40.200 --> 06:45.300
OK, BUT WHAT ABOUT
HER PERSONALITY
MAKES HER YOUR IDEAL WOMAN?

06:45.300 --> 06:47.400
WELL, SHE'S PRETTY,
LIKE I SAID,

06:47.400 --> 06:53.000
AND SHE CAN WALK
REALLY GOOD, AND
SHE'S GOT THIS...

06:53.000 --> 06:55.400
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST GO ASK JACK.

06:55.400 --> 06:56.967
I MEAN, HE'S THE ONE
WHO WON HER.

06:56.967 --> 06:58.400
YOU KNOW,
IT SOUNDS TO ME

06:58.400 --> 07:00.066
LIKE YOU CARE MORE
ABOUT THE COMPETITION
WITH JACK

07:00.066 --> 07:01.300
THAN YOU ACTUALLY
CARE ABOUT HER.

07:01.300 --> 07:02.967
OH, WELL, NOW, SEE,
THAT IS RIDICULOUS.

07:02.967 --> 07:05.000
I COULD'VE WON THAT.
I COULD. I SWEAR.

07:05.000 --> 07:06.467
HE CHEATED.

07:06.467 --> 07:07.934
BECAUSE DAD DIED?

07:07.934 --> 07:10.100
YEAH. YEAH. YEAH.
I MEAN, HE WAS GRIEVING.

07:10.100 --> 07:11.934
CHICKS TOTALLY DIG
PEOPLE THAT ARE GRIEVING.

07:11.934 --> 07:13.900
NOW DON'T GET ME WRONG.
I KNOW IT WAS YOUR DAD
AND EVERYTHING, I REALLY DO,

07:13.900 --> 07:16.767
BUT I'M PRETTY SURE
IT WAS A FIX.

07:16.767 --> 07:19.100
ERIC, YOU KNOW,
I FEEL REALLY GOOD

07:19.100 --> 07:20.767
ABOUT MY LIFE
RIGHT NOW.

07:20.767 --> 07:22.800
BECAUSE WHEN I
TOOK OFF
IN MY DAD'S TRAILER,

07:22.800 --> 07:24.600
I HAD A MOMENT,
JUST ONE MOMENT,

07:24.600 --> 07:27.100
THAT MADE EVERYTHING
COMPLETELY CLEAR
FOR ME.

07:27.100 --> 07:29.033
I WAS LOOKING
AT THE NIGHT SKY,

07:29.033 --> 07:31.233
AND I COULD SEE
EVERYTHING--

07:31.233 --> 07:35.734
THE STARS, PLANETS,
GALAXIES.

07:35.734 --> 07:38.700
YOU MUST'VE FELT
SO SMALL.

07:38.700 --> 07:41.567
I DID.
I TOTALLY DID.
I FELT LIKE A SPECK

07:41.567 --> 07:44.100
WHO WAS HERE FOR
ONE MOMENT IN TIME

07:44.100 --> 07:46.133
AND THEN GONE.

07:46.133 --> 07:47.867
AND I DECIDED THAT
WHILE I'M HERE,

07:47.867 --> 07:49.500
I WANNA BE
WITH MY FRIENDS

07:49.500 --> 07:50.667
AND THE PEOPLE
I LOVE.

07:53.500 --> 07:54.734
BECAUSE WHEN
I'M WITH YOU GUYS,

07:54.734 --> 07:56.300
I DON'T FEEL
THAT SMALL.

07:59.100 --> 08:00.400
THAT'S WHAT
I FIGURED OUT.

08:02.467 --> 08:05.300
BUT THAT'S...FOR YOU?

08:05.300 --> 08:07.500
YEAH, THAT'S FOR ME.

08:07.500 --> 08:10.567
SO, I GUESS I GOT
TO FIGURE STUFF OUT, TOO,

08:10.567 --> 08:12.367
BUT...FOR ME.

08:12.367 --> 08:14.100
FOR YOU.

08:14.100 --> 08:16.600
I'M GLAD
YOU CAME BACK, SHAWN.

08:16.600 --> 08:18.600
WAS A NICE TALK.

08:18.600 --> 08:19.900
YEAH, IT WAS.

08:19.900 --> 08:22.467
WE SHOULD DO THIS
AGAIN SOMETIME.

08:26.667 --> 08:30.033
LOOK AT THEM, CORY.
THAT IS ONE BIG,
HAPPY FAMILY.

08:30.033 --> 08:33.567
SEE, I LOOK AT THEM,
AND THAT'S HOW I KNOW
WE'RE GOING TO BE OK.

08:33.567 --> 08:34.667
THAT'S HOW.

08:34.667 --> 08:37.200
AND MY CARDS
ARE WORKING
LIKE A CHARM.

08:37.200 --> 08:38.700
YEAH, WHATEVER.

08:38.700 --> 08:40.867
CARDS? CORY,
WHAT DID YOU DO?

08:40.867 --> 08:42.934
SHH.

08:45.000 --> 08:46.900
HELLO.

08:46.900 --> 08:48.834
HI.
HI, HOW ARE YA?

08:48.834 --> 08:49.967
WHAT ARE WE
TALKING ABOUT?

08:49.967 --> 08:51.233
TELEVISION.

08:51.233 --> 08:53.233
JEDEDIAH SAYS THERE'S
NOTHING GOOD ON ANYMORE.

08:53.233 --> 08:54.967
TELEVISION?

08:54.967 --> 08:57.700
IS TELEVISION BRIDGES
OR PATIO FURNITURE,
DAD?

08:57.700 --> 09:00.100
THE ONLY GOOD SHOW
THAT WAS EVER
ON TELEVISION,

09:00.100 --> 09:02.033
AND EVERYBODY KNOWS
THIS, IS <i>ALF. </i>

09:02.033 --> 09:03.233
OH, WHAT?

09:03.233 --> 09:05.400
NOBODY WATCHES
<i>ALF, </i>JEDEDIAH.

09:05.400 --> 09:06.667
IT'S NOT EVEN
ON ANYMORE.

09:06.667 --> 09:08.233
WELL, THAT'S MY POINT,
RHIANNON.

09:08.233 --> 09:09.467
THERE'S NOTHING GOOD
ON TELEVISION.

09:09.467 --> 09:11.233
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH--YES.
<i>ALLY McBEAL? </i>

09:11.233 --> 09:13.700
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT'S WRONG
WITH <i>ALLY McBEAL. </i>

09:13.700 --> 09:15.767
SHE HAS NO PASSION
FOR THE LAW.
WHAT?!

09:15.767 --> 09:18.200
AND SHE TAKES ISSUE
WITH HER HUSBAND'S
COMMENTS

09:18.200 --> 09:20.500
ON TELEVISION IN FRONT
OF OTHER PEOPLE.

09:20.500 --> 09:23.800
SHE'S NOT EVEN MARRIED.
AND SHE NEVER WILL BE.

09:23.800 --> 09:26.467
YOU REMEMBER WHEN
ALF WAS ON <i>JOHNNY CARSON? </i>

09:26.467 --> 09:27.567
OH, NO.

09:27.567 --> 09:29.400
BOY, NOBODY DID IT
LIKE JOHNNY.

09:29.400 --> 09:31.000
DAD.

09:31.000 --> 09:32.734
[IMITATING CARSON]
OOH, I DID NOT
KNOW THAT.

09:37.767 --> 09:39.767
WELL, THAT WAS...
THAT WAS HIDEOUS.

09:39.767 --> 09:41.367
DO ANOTHER ONE.

09:41.367 --> 09:42.767
I DON'T REALLY WANT TO NOW.

09:42.767 --> 09:46.500
JEDEDIAH, I THOUGHT
HIS JOHNNY CARSON
WAS ABSOLUTELY FINE.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.834
[IMITATING ED McMAHON]
HEY-OOOOOO. HAW HAW.

09:48.834 --> 09:50.467
YOU ARE CORRECT, SIR.

09:50.467 --> 09:53.900
HAW HAW HAW.
OH, NO. OH, MY GOD.

09:53.900 --> 09:55.300
OH, NO. OH, NO.

09:55.300 --> 09:57.800
RHIANNON, I WAS JUST HAVING A
LITTLE FUN.

09:57.800 --> 09:59.767
COME ON, DAD. LET'S HEAR
YOUR JOHNNY CARSON.

09:59.767 --> 10:01.200
WHY IS IT,
NO MATTER
WHAT I SAY,

10:01.200 --> 10:04.233
YOU HAVE TO TAKE
THE OPPOSITE
POINT OF VIEW?

10:04.233 --> 10:05.400
[BABY CRIES]

10:05.400 --> 10:06.834
I DIDN'T MEAN TO SCOLD.

10:06.834 --> 10:08.467
I JUST THOUGHT
YOU WERE BEING
A LITTLE RUDE.

10:08.467 --> 10:09.900
NO, I WASN'T BEING RUDE.

10:09.900 --> 10:12.800
RUDE IS HOW YOU CHOSE
TO INTERPRET IT...HONEY.

10:12.800 --> 10:16.100
♪ HUSH, LITTLE BABY,
DON'T SAY A WORD ♪

10:16.100 --> 10:19.133
MOM? MOM! MOM! MOM!

10:19.133 --> 10:22.200
[IMITATING HUMPHREY BOGART]
OF ALL THE GIN JOINTS
IN ALL THE TOWNS

10:22.200 --> 10:24.567
IN ALL THE WORLD,
SHE WALKS INTO MINE.

10:24.567 --> 10:27.967
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

10:27.967 --> 10:30.500
LET'S JUST DROP THIS
FOR NOW AND TALK
ABOUT IT LATER, OK?

10:30.500 --> 10:31.600
JUST DROP IT.

10:31.600 --> 10:34.000
THE TROUBLE WITH US
IS WE DROP SOMETHING,

10:34.000 --> 10:36.100
IT DOESN'T MEAN
IT GOES AWAY.

10:37.600 --> 10:40.233
OH, COR, UM,
HOW ABOUT SOME DESSERT?

10:40.233 --> 10:43.200
[IMITATING JACK BENNY]
HOW ABOUT A LITTLE,
UH, DESSERT?

10:44.934 --> 10:46.667
I THINK THAT SOUNDS
LIKE A GREAT IDEA,

10:46.667 --> 10:48.767
BECAUSE, UH, CORY AND I
HAVE AN ANNOUNCEMENT TO MAKE.

10:48.767 --> 10:51.233
HONEY, I WANNA HEAR
YOUR ANNOUNCEMENT.
I REALLY DO.

10:51.233 --> 10:53.133
BUT I GOTTA TAKE
A WALK FOR
A FEW MINUTES,

10:53.133 --> 10:54.200
GET A LITTLE AIR.

10:54.200 --> 10:55.934
YEAH, WHY DON'T YOU
DO THAT?

10:57.000 --> 10:58.600
[DOOR SLAMS]
MOM?

10:58.600 --> 11:00.567
OH, I'M SORRY.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.400
YOU JUST COULDN'T
STICK TO THE CARDS,
COULD YA?

11:14.600 --> 11:16.600
MOM, WHAT'S WRONG?

11:16.600 --> 11:18.600
IT'S NOTHING, TOPANGA.
I'M EMOTIONAL.

11:18.600 --> 11:21.133
MY--MY LITTLE GIRL
IS GETTING MARRIED.

11:21.133 --> 11:22.600
WHAT'S WRONG WITH DAD?

11:22.600 --> 11:26.700
OH, DADDY AND I
HAVE BEEN TOGETHER
A LONG TIME.

11:26.700 --> 11:28.700
I KNOW. THAT'S WHAT
I KEEP TELLING CORY.

11:28.700 --> 11:30.400
HE REALLY WANTS ME
TO REASSURE HIM

11:30.400 --> 11:32.567
THAT OUR RELATIONSHIP
IS GOING TO LAST FOREVER.

11:32.567 --> 11:36.500
ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS TELL HIM ABOUT YOU GUYS.

11:36.500 --> 11:39.033
TOPANGA...

11:39.033 --> 11:40.867
EVERY RELATIONSHIP
LIVES ON ITS OWN.

11:40.867 --> 11:43.667
WHAT YOU EACH
BRING TO IT
IS WHAT SUSTAINS IT.

11:43.667 --> 11:45.500
YOU DON'T NEED
TO LOOK AT ANY
OTHER RELATIONSHIP

11:45.500 --> 11:46.667
AS AN EXAMPLE.

11:46.667 --> 11:48.300
YOU'RE RIGHT.

11:48.300 --> 11:52.367
IT'S GOING TO BE
REALLY HARD FOR ME AND CORY
TO LIVE UP TO YOU GUYS,

11:52.367 --> 11:53.600
BUT WE'RE GONNA TRY.

11:55.500 --> 11:57.100
SORRY I WALKED OUT
LIKE THAT.

11:57.100 --> 11:58.700
IT WAS A LONG DRIVE
FROM PITTSBURGH.

11:58.700 --> 11:59.800
I'M A LITTLE WORN OUT.

11:59.800 --> 12:01.100
IT'S OK, DADDY.

12:01.100 --> 12:02.667
ARE WE READY
TO GO BACK INSIDE?

12:02.667 --> 12:03.934
WE HAVE A WEDDING
TO PLAN.

12:03.934 --> 12:05.200
YEAH.

12:08.133 --> 12:10.500
YOU GET ENOUGH AIR, JED?

12:16.100 --> 12:18.000
I'M MAKING SPAGHETTI.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.800
YOU WANNA SHARE IT LIKE
<i>LADY AND THE TRAMP? </i>

12:19.800 --> 12:21.800
YEAH.
I'LL BE TRAMP.

12:21.800 --> 12:23.767
UNLESS, UH,
YOU WANNA BE?

12:23.767 --> 12:26.033
WELL...

12:28.100 --> 12:29.767
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

12:29.767 --> 12:30.767
OH, NUTS!

12:30.767 --> 12:31.934
WHO IS IT?

12:31.934 --> 12:33.000
IT'S ERIC.

12:33.000 --> 12:35.700
UH, JUST A SECOND.

12:35.700 --> 12:37.400
OK.

12:41.200 --> 12:42.834
HEY.
HEY.

12:42.834 --> 12:44.900
SO, WHAT HAVE
YOU GUYS BEEN UP TO?

12:44.900 --> 12:46.500
OH, NOTHING. IT WAS
JUST A NORMAL NIGHT.

12:46.500 --> 12:48.300
I GUESS I'M NOT
INTERRUPTING
ANYTHING HERE.

12:48.300 --> 12:51.900
OH, NO, NO. WE WERE JUST,
UH, READING.
THE BIBLE.

12:51.900 --> 12:53.567
OH, WELL, THAT'S GOOD

12:53.567 --> 12:55.900
'CAUSE I ACTUALLY
CAME HERE TO GIVE YOU
MY BLESSING. HA HA.

12:55.900 --> 12:57.900
NO, I JUST WANTED
TO TELL YOU GUYS

12:57.900 --> 12:59.934
THAT I'M NOT GONNA TRY
TO MAKE YOU FEEL
UNCOMFORTABLE OR BAD--

12:59.934 --> 13:03.200
2 STRAWS!
IT'S OK. IT'S OK.

13:03.200 --> 13:04.767
YOU KNOW, SERIOUSLY,
FORGET ABOUT THAT.

13:04.767 --> 13:07.100
I JUST WANTED
TO SAY THAT...

13:07.100 --> 13:10.700
I AM GENUINELY
HAPPY FOR BOTH OF YOU.

13:10.700 --> 13:14.233
OH, UM,
ISN'T THAT NICE.

13:14.233 --> 13:15.734
WHY?

13:15.734 --> 13:17.834
YOU'RE GONNA GET A KICK
OUT OF THIS. YOU ARE.

13:17.834 --> 13:21.000
YOU REMEMBER HOW
EXCITED WE WERE
WHEN SHE MOVED IN?

13:21.000 --> 13:24.000
YEAH.
MAYBE THIS SHOULD JUST
BE BETWEEN YOU GUYS.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.200
NO, NO, THAT'S
OK. LISTEN.

13:25.200 --> 13:26.800
REMEMBER HOW,
FROM THE SECOND
WE SAW HER,

13:26.800 --> 13:27.800
WE BOTH
WANTED HER?

13:27.800 --> 13:29.000
YEAH.

13:29.000 --> 13:30.467
UM, I'M GONNA
LEAVE NOW, OK?

13:30.467 --> 13:32.667
NO, NO. LISTEN,
LISTEN, 'CAUSE
HERE'S THE THING.

13:32.667 --> 13:35.767
I HAVE BEEN A FOOL.

13:35.767 --> 13:37.367
WHAT?

13:37.367 --> 13:39.400
THIS WHOLE TIME,
I'VE BEEN SITTING
HERE THINKING

13:39.400 --> 13:41.800
I'M SO IN LOVE
WITH RACHEL, BUT...

13:41.800 --> 13:44.233
I DON'T EVEN
KNOW HER.
WHAT?

13:44.233 --> 13:47.033
YEAH, JUST LIVING
IN THE SAME APARTMENT
WITH HER, YOU KNOW,

13:47.033 --> 13:49.467
WONDERING WHAT SHE'S
GONNA WEAR EVERY DAY

13:49.467 --> 13:52.000
OR CATCHING A WHIFF
OF THE SMELL OF HER HAIR

13:52.000 --> 13:54.967
OR THAT CUTE, FUNNY
LITTLE LAUGH SHE'S GOT.

13:54.967 --> 13:56.300
[GIGGLING]

13:56.300 --> 13:57.967
OH, YOU MEAN
LIKE THAT.

13:57.967 --> 14:01.400
YEAH, OUR LIVES REALLY
WERE TURNED UPSIDE DOWN
BY THIS ONE.

14:01.400 --> 14:02.934
OH, DUDE, WEREN'T THEY?
I'M TELLING YOU, MAN.

14:02.934 --> 14:04.500
BUT YOU KNOW
SOMETHING,

14:04.500 --> 14:06.600
I REALIZED SOMETHING
AFTER I MOVED OUT
OF THE APARTMENT.

14:06.600 --> 14:08.767
WHAT?
IT WAS THE COMPETITION,

14:08.767 --> 14:10.300
THE COMPETITION
THAT WAS SO EXCITING!

14:10.300 --> 14:12.834
YEAH, IT WAS.
WHAT?

14:12.834 --> 14:14.767
YEAH, YEAH,
I WON THAT ONE.

14:14.767 --> 14:16.000
YEAH.

14:16.000 --> 14:17.100
WON WHAT?

14:17.100 --> 14:18.300
WON YOU.

14:18.300 --> 14:20.834
NO, I MEAN,
I DIDN'T "WON" YOU.

14:20.834 --> 14:23.767
I MEANT
I...WON YOUUUU.

14:25.133 --> 14:27.867
WELL, ANYWAY, LOOK,

14:27.867 --> 14:30.600
I REALLY JUST
CAME OVER HERE...

14:30.600 --> 14:34.100
TO TELL YOU GUYS
HOW HAPPY I AM FOR YOU,
YOU KNOW?

14:34.100 --> 14:36.834
IT FEELS SO GOOD
TO FINALLY GET IT
OFF MY CHEST.

14:36.834 --> 14:42.100
SO...WHEW, ALL RIGHT,
THAT'S--THAT'S ALL.
I'M GONNA GO NOW.

14:42.100 --> 14:44.033
UM, HEY, IT WAS GOOD
SEEING YOU AGAIN, MAN.

14:44.033 --> 14:45.934
REALLY, IT WAS GOOD
SEEING YA, ALL RIGHT?

14:45.934 --> 14:47.500
SEE YA, SWEETIE,
ALL RIGHT.

14:47.500 --> 14:49.500
PEACE.

14:52.367 --> 14:54.934
HOW YA DOING?

14:54.934 --> 14:56.567
HI.

15:00.233 --> 15:01.233
SO, WHILE YOU GUYS
ARE HERE,

15:01.233 --> 15:02.734
WE WANT YOU TO COME
DOWN AND SEE THE HALL

15:02.734 --> 15:03.967
WHERE WE WANT
TO GET MARRIED.

15:03.967 --> 15:05.700
IT IS SO BEAUTIFUL.
WE WILL, HONEY.

15:05.700 --> 15:07.367
WE NEVER ACTUALLY
HAD A HALL.

15:07.367 --> 15:08.867
WE ELOPED.
YOU DID?

15:08.867 --> 15:11.100
YEAH, HER FOLKS
DIDN'T THINK I'D
AMOUNT TO ANYTHING,

15:11.100 --> 15:13.600
BUT I GUESS
WE SHOWED THEM,
HUH, HONEY?

15:13.600 --> 15:15.500
I GUESS.

15:15.500 --> 15:19.033
23 YEARS
OF HAPPINESS,
A BRAND-NEW BABY,

15:19.033 --> 15:21.100
THESE BABIES
GETTING MARRIED...

15:21.100 --> 15:22.700
YEAH, WE SHOWED 'EM.

15:27.367 --> 15:28.700
WHAT ABOUT YOU GUYS?

15:28.700 --> 15:31.233
DID GRANDMA AND GRANDPA
THINK YOU GUYS
WOULD MAKE IT?

15:31.233 --> 15:33.900
YEAH, THEY THOUGHT
WE WOULD MAKE IT.

15:33.900 --> 15:36.800
THEY THOUGHT WE WOULD
BE TOGETHER FOREVER.

15:36.800 --> 15:38.133
DON'T.

15:38.133 --> 15:39.800
SO DID I.
OH, HONEY...

15:39.800 --> 15:40.800
MOM?

15:40.800 --> 15:42.567
[CRYING]
I'M SORRY.

15:42.567 --> 15:44.500
RHIANNON, NOT NOW.

15:44.500 --> 15:46.500
MOM, WHY ARE YOU
CRYING LIKE THIS?
YOU'RE SCARING ME.

15:46.500 --> 15:49.033
I THOUGHT I COULD
GET THROUGH THIS,
BUT I CAN'T.

15:49.033 --> 15:50.200
I'M SO SORRY.

15:50.200 --> 15:51.734
NO, ACTUALLY,
YOU KNOW WHAT,

15:51.734 --> 15:53.000
IT'S TIME TO FEED
THE BABY.

15:53.000 --> 15:55.000
ALAN, WHY DON'T
YOU COME HELP ME
FEED THE BABY.

15:55.000 --> 15:56.467
HOW CAN I HELP
YOU FEED THE...

15:56.467 --> 15:57.600
ALAN...

15:57.600 --> 15:59.300
OH, YES, OF COURSE.

15:59.300 --> 16:02.567
I'M SURE I CAN HELP,
UM...EXCUSE US.

16:02.567 --> 16:03.767
HERE, MAYBE
I SHOULD GO...

16:03.767 --> 16:05.667
NO, NO, CORY.
PLEASE, YOU STAY.

16:05.667 --> 16:06.834
IF YOU STAY,
I DON'T THINK--

16:06.834 --> 16:08.400
YOUR FATHER
AND I ARGUE A LOT.

16:08.400 --> 16:10.867
THAT SHE'D ACTUALLY
SAY ANYTHING
IN FRONT OF YOU.

16:10.867 --> 16:13.100
ALL MARRIED COUPLES
ARGUE A LOT.

16:13.100 --> 16:15.767
TOPANGA, HAVEN'T YOU
EVER WONDERED WHY
WE LET YOU STAY HERE

16:15.767 --> 16:16.934
WHEN WE MOVED
TO PITTSBURGH?

16:16.934 --> 16:18.567
BECAUSE OF ME.

16:18.567 --> 16:19.800
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO TAKE ME AWAY

16:19.800 --> 16:20.867
FROM MY LAST YEAR
OF HIGH SCHOOL.

16:20.867 --> 16:22.367
AND CORY.

16:22.367 --> 16:24.233
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO RIP ME AWAY
FROM MY FRIENDS.

16:24.233 --> 16:25.400
ME.
DADDY AND I THOUGHT

16:25.400 --> 16:26.600
WE COULD WORK
THINGS OUT BETTER

16:26.600 --> 16:27.934
IF WE TOOK SOME TIME
BY OURSELVES.

16:27.934 --> 16:30.600
WORK WHAT OUT?
THERE'S NOBODY
LIKE YOU TWO.

16:30.600 --> 16:31.667
YOU TWO
ARE SO IN LOVE.

16:31.667 --> 16:33.734
TOPANGA, PEOPLE CHANGE.

16:33.734 --> 16:35.400
DADDY, WHY IS MOM
TALKING LIKE THIS?

16:35.400 --> 16:36.600
WE DIDN'T WANT TO
DUMP THIS ON YOU.

16:36.600 --> 16:38.567
WE WANTED TO WAIT
UNTIL AFTER
THE WEDDING.

16:38.567 --> 16:40.300
HONEY, LOOK, WE
TRIED. WE TRIED
AS HARD AS WE---

16:40.300 --> 16:41.600
YOU GUYS WILL
GET THROUGH THIS.

16:41.600 --> 16:45.133
MARRIAGE IS NOT SOMETHING
TO GET THROUGH, TOPANGA!

16:45.133 --> 16:48.567
THAT'S NOT WHY
I GOT MARRIED.

16:48.567 --> 16:50.967
OH, GOD.
NO, GOD. OH, GOD.

16:50.967 --> 16:55.200
OH, SWEETHEART,
I'M--I'M--
YOUR DADDY AND I...

16:58.200 --> 17:01.300
MAYBE WE JUST
GOT MARRIED
TOO YOUNG.

17:01.300 --> 17:03.567
JED!

17:03.567 --> 17:04.600
NOT YOU.

17:07.200 --> 17:09.500
THIS HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOU.

17:19.467 --> 17:22.000
NOW REMEMBER,
WE ARE NOT HERE
AS A COUPLE.

17:22.000 --> 17:23.934
I'LL SIT WITH YOU,
I MAY DANCE WITH YOU,

17:23.934 --> 17:25.200
BUT WE ARE NOT TOGETHER.

17:25.200 --> 17:28.200
I KNOW. I KNOW.
YOU REMINDED ME
3 TIMES IN THE CAR.

17:28.200 --> 17:31.200
DON'T WORRY.
THE ONLY FEELINGS
I HAVE FOR YOU

17:31.200 --> 17:33.600
ARE FRIENDLY FEELINGS.
OK, BUT IT'S A WEDDING.

17:33.600 --> 17:35.033
I DON'T WANT
YOU GETTING
ALL SAPPY ON ME.

17:35.033 --> 17:36.300
OH, COME ON.

17:36.300 --> 17:38.500
AM I THE SAPPY TYPE?

17:38.500 --> 17:42.200
OH, MORGAN'S
A FLOWER GIRL.

17:42.200 --> 17:44.200
GIMME KISSEE.

17:44.200 --> 17:46.033
I'M REALLY
GONNA MISS YOU,
MR. FEENY.

17:46.033 --> 17:48.000
OH, I'LL MISS YOU,
TOO, MY BOY.

17:48.000 --> 17:50.467
BUT I'LL BE BACK
FROM ARUBA IN 2 WEEKS.

17:50.467 --> 17:54.867
YEAH, I'M, UH,
THINKING OF DOING
SOME TRAVELING MYSELF.

17:54.867 --> 17:58.667
OH, NO, DON'T WORRY.
I'M NOT GOING TO ARUBA.

17:58.667 --> 18:00.834
I LOVE YOU, MR. FEENY.

18:03.700 --> 18:06.000
I LOVE YOU, TOO, ERIC.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.300
I'LL SEE YOU
WHEN I GET BACK.

18:08.300 --> 18:10.500
YEAH.
I'LL SEE YA.

18:12.600 --> 18:14.967
<i>[THE WEDDING MARCH] </i>

18:30.467 --> 18:32.600
WE ARE GATHERED HERE TODAY

18:32.600 --> 18:35.133
TO JOIN THIS COUPLE
IN HOLY MATRIMONY,

18:35.133 --> 18:37.233
WHICH IS
AN HONORABLE ESTATE.

18:37.233 --> 18:40.100
GEORGE AND LILA HAVE CHOSEN

18:40.100 --> 18:43.300
TO EXPRESS THEIR LOVE
IN THEIR OWN WORDS.

18:45.467 --> 18:50.500
QUIETLY, I HAVE
SEARCHED FOR LOVE
FOR MUCH OF MY LIFE.

18:50.500 --> 18:55.100
AND NOW THAT I BEGIN
THIS MARRIAGE
OF OUR SPIRITS,

18:55.100 --> 19:00.066
I REALIZE HOW
INCREDIBLY LUCKY
I AM...

19:00.066 --> 19:02.600
TO HAVE FOUND IT.

19:02.600 --> 19:04.500
MY ONLY SADNESS

19:04.500 --> 19:08.400
IS THAT I FOUND YOU
SO LATE IN LIFE...

19:10.233 --> 19:12.834
THAT WE'VE LIVED OUR LIVES

19:12.834 --> 19:15.967
SPENDING MORE DAYS
APART THAN TOGETHER.

19:15.967 --> 19:19.000
BUT YOU'VE GIVEN ME
YOUR LOVE
AND FRIENDSHIP,

19:19.000 --> 19:22.200
AND I PROMISE
I'LL MAKE UP FOR
THAT LOST TIME.

19:22.200 --> 19:27.300
FOR MARRIAGE IS BASED
ON THOSE THINGS,

19:27.300 --> 19:31.467
BUT FRIENDSHIP
MOST OF ALL.

19:31.467 --> 19:36.300
DO YOU, GEORGE FEENY,
TAKE LILA BOLANDER AS
YOUR LAWFUL WEDDED WIFE,

19:36.300 --> 19:39.700
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD
UNTIL DEATH DO YOU PART?

19:39.700 --> 19:41.367
George: I DO.

19:41.367 --> 19:45.700
AND DO YOU, LILA BOLANDER,
TAKE GEORGE FEENY AS
YOUR LAWFUL WEDDED HUSBAND,

19:45.700 --> 19:49.834
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD
UNTIL DEATH DO YOU PART?

19:49.834 --> 19:51.734
Lila: I DO.

19:51.734 --> 19:56.000
WITH THE POWERS
VESTED IN ME,
I NOW PRONOUNCE YOU

19:56.000 --> 19:57.700
HUSBAND AND WIFE.

19:57.700 --> 19:59.100
YOU MAY KISS THE BRIDE.

20:11.100 --> 20:12.700
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

20:12.700 --> 20:14.934
HELLO.

20:14.934 --> 20:16.867
OH, HEY,
MR. RUTHERFORD.

20:16.867 --> 20:20.367
NO, NO, NO, I'M SORRY
WE HAVEN'T GOTTEN BACK
TO YOU YET.

20:26.567 --> 20:28.934
NO, I DON'T THINK
JULY IS GOING TO WORK.

20:31.367 --> 20:33.800
YEAH, I--I GUESS WE'RE
STILL THINKING ABOUT IT.

20:36.200 --> 20:37.900
YEAH.

20:37.900 --> 20:39.867
OK, THANK YOU.
